    {
      "text": "MONTHLY NEWS RELEASE INFLATION REPORT ON MARCH, EFY 2017",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 144.62,
        "y0": 687.05164,
        "x1": 466.71896000000004,
        "y1": 642.7464561283851
      },
      "block_type": "section_header"
    },
    {
      "text": "Issue No. 21/2017",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 213.65,
        "y0": 634.67764,
        "x1": 305.47123999999997,
        "y1": 625.0763598395185
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "1. Summary",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 166.34,
        "y0": 612.4183599999999,
        "x1": 247.88,
        "y1": 598.8840253159478
      },
      "block_type": "section_header"
    },
    {
      "text": "The  Consumer  Price  Index  (CPI),  a  key  economic  statistics,  is  surveyed,  analyzed,  and made available to data users on a monthly basis.",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 161.86550473451152,
        "y0": 585.59764,
        "x1": 577.5490514120002,
        "y1": 557.9963598395185
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "The year -on -year, general inflation rate (annual percentage change) in the country stood at 13.6 percent for the month of March EFY2017. A year earlier (in March EFY2016), the rate was 26.2 percent. The month -on -month general inflation rate increased by 2.7 percent for the month of March -EFY2017. It was 4.0 percent in March EFY2016.",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 161.86426498688385,
        "y0": 549.6170559999999,
        "x1": 578.0354314120001,
        "y1": 485.96635983951853
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "General inflation encompasses of two main divisions and twenty -one groups of expenditures.  These divisions registered the following price changes during the month of March EFY2017 compared with March EFY2016.",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 161.86550473451152,
        "y0": 477.56764,
        "x1": 577.5888914120004,
        "y1": 431.96635983951853
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "2. Food & Non -alcoholic Beverages and Non -Food Inflation (Year -on -Year)",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 159.98,
        "y0": 410.76135999999997,
        "x1": 525.89776,
        "y1": 400.11897717151453
      },
      "block_type": "section_header"
    },
    {
      "text": "The year -on -year inflation and the month -to -month inflation rates helps to gauge the current inflation trajectory, as they capture short -term fluctuations in prices and provides an immediate indicator of inflationary pressures. Particularly, the month -to -month is also crucial  for  monitoring  changes  in  consumer  prices  and  identifying  any  sudden  spikes  or  declines in inflation.",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 159.98,
        "y0": 383.86705600000005,
        "x1": 575.4547600000002,
        "y1": 302.2263598395185
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "Food & Non -alcoholic Beverages index",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 158.18,
        "y0": 293.38136,
        "x1": 349.58167999999984,
        "y1": 282.73897717151453
      },
      "block_type": "section_header"
    },
    {
      "text": "The year -on -year  inflation  rate,  also  known  as  the  annual  inflation  rate,  measures  the  percentage change in overall price levels from one year to the same month in the previous year. Accordingly, the year -on -year inflation rate of the Food and Non -alcoholic component of the CPI, for the month of March  2017 EFY stood at 11.9%. This implies that the CPI of Food and Non -Alcoholic Beverages has, on average, increased by 11.9% compared to March EFY2016. The major contributing factors for the rise of food inflation for  March EFY2017 was the observed increase in the average prices of major food commodities such as bread and cereals (1.2%), vegetables (6.1%), meat (17.8%), Sugar, jam, honey & chocolate (28.8%),  Milk, Cheese and Eggs  (8.2%), Oils and Fats (36.3%), Fruit (13.4%),  and Food products n.e.c (26.7%).",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 158.18,
        "y0": 273.66764,
        "x1": 579.5615200000001,
        "y1": 120.03635983951858
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "www.ess.gov.et",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 1,
        "x0": 477.58,
        "y0": 62.375999999999976,
        "x1": 558.4720000000001,
        "y1": 51.157190839694636
      },
      "block_type": "page_footer"
    },
    {
