        "x1": 378.5251760000001,
        "y1": 710.4865692517552
      },
      "block_type": "section_header"
    },
    {
      "text": "As can be seen from the above figure, the non - food year - on - year inflation rate increased in March - ETY2017 as compared to last month while the Food inflation decreased in magnitude. The Non - Food inflation increased by 16.2 percent in the same period. Particularly, Alcoholic Beverages and Tobacco increased by (15.2%); Housing, water, electricity & other fuel component (17.4%); Furnishings, house- hold equipment & routine maintenance of the House (15.4%);   Health (12.7%); Transport (32.5%); Com- munication (2.0%); Education (23.3%);  Restaurants and hotels (18.3%) and Miscellaneous goods and services (18.4%) have contributed for the rise in non - food inflation rate in March EFY2017.",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 3,
        "x0": 39.48,
        "y0": 239.98136,
        "x1": 548.7097600000001,
        "y1": 138.22897717151454
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
