    {
      "text": "Major sub divisions in the food and non -food commodities (year -on -Year).",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 4,
        "x0": 48.96,
        "y0": 624.088,
        "x1": 447.15400000000005,
        "y1": 612.5201925777332
      },
      "block_type": "section_header"
    },
    {
      "text": "When we look at major division of food and non -food commodities, which holds large share in the commodity basket, the magnitude of inflation rate at March EFY2017 showed a declining situation for Food as compared to the previous month.  From Food and Non -Alcoholic Beverage aspect, the highest weight is hold by Bread and Cereals, Vegetables, Other -Food products, Non -Alcoholic Beverage, and Meat; whose inflation at March EFY2017 is recorded  an increase for Bread & Cereals (1.2%);  Vegetables  (6.1%);  Other -Food products (Food products not elsewhere classified)  (26.7%); Meat (17.8%) and Non -Alcoholic Beverages & coffee (50.2%).",
      "bbox": {
        "page": 4,
        "x0": 48.96,
        "y0": 602.79136,
        "x1": 547.18,
        "y1": 473.19897717151457
      },
      "block_type": "text"
    },
    {
      "text": "Similarly, during March 2017 EFY the year -on -year inflation rate of the major Non -Food items of Housing, Water, Electricity, Gas, & Other Fuels (17.4%) ; Restaurants and Hotels (18.3%) ; Alcoholic  Beverages  &  Tobacco (15.2%) ;  Furnishings,  Household  Equipment  &  Routine  Household Maintenance of the House (15.4%) and Clothing and Footwear (8.7%).",
      "bbox": {
